author: Louise Boyle In Delphi
title: Teen girls double murder: FBI step up hunt in Indiana | Daily Mail Online
text: show ad EXCLUSIVE: FBI and Homeland Security experts step up hunt for murderer of two teenage girls - as mystery man seen on trail where they died is STILL not found Abigail Williams, 13, and Liberty German, 14, were found murdered on Tuesday, the day after they went for a hike on a scenic trail Department of Homeland Security and FBI experts are being called in to the hunt for their killer Police have issued picture of man they want to speak to who was on the bridge 'around the same time' as the teens Officer tells DailyMail.com they have had hundreds of tips on who he might be but are still to find him and say he is NOT being called a suspect Picture is only known lead in the investigation which has been made public by law enforcement - who have yet to say how teenagers were killed Police have also not said if girls' phones have been recovered or who took the pictue of the mystery man Case has drawn comparisons to 80s movie Stand By Me Published: 17:35 GMT, 16 February 2017 | Updated: 00:50 GMT, 17 February 2017 115 shares
